A possible issue would be that, with the lack of new worlds to live on,
civilizations that rise and fall would have be rebuild on the ruins of
the older civilizations.  If this happens over trillions of years, one
may end up with situations where later civilizations -- especially when
they've been reborn on the ashes of countless past ones -- could make it
hard for later civilizations to be as productive as the previous ones.

