The problem with a simple Jeans escape solution here is the long
timescales... very long timescales, for a slight change in the escape
velocity / RMS velocity ratio. For Vesc/Vrms = 5, you've got roughly
10's of millions of years of atmosphere. For Vesc/Vrms = 6, that jumps
to billions, and for Vesc/Vrms = 7 or greater, the atmosphere will
last longer than even the red dwarf. Assuming pure Jeans escape,
anyway.

